            <div class="product">
                <h3>Entry Signals</h3>
                <p>To enter a position, pay close attention to the correlation signals from the major indicators:</p>
                <h4>BUY Signal Criteria:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>The red MA line (main graph) crosses above the green line.</li>
                    <li>Momentum crosses the 100 mark upwards.</li>
                    <li>The green UTPOW line crosses above the red line and is rising.</li>
                    <li>The yellow TRAP line is rising and below the green histogram.</li>
                    <li>MACD crosses above the zero line.</li>
                </ol>
                <h4>SELL Signal Criteria:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>The red MA line (main graph) crosses below the green line.</li>
                    <li>Momentum crosses the 100 mark downwards.</li>
                    <li>The green UTPOW line crosses below the red line and is falling.</li>
                    <li>The yellow TRAP line is falling and below the red histogram.</li>
                    <li>MACD crosses below the zero line.</li>
                </ol>
                <h3>Risk Management</h3>
                <p>To manage risk effectively, consider the following:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Stop-loss: Recommended not lower than 40-50 pips.</li>
                    <li>Take-profit: Recommended not lower than 30 pips.</li>
                    <li>Trailing Stop: Once you've achieved 30-40 pips in profit, consider moving the stop-loss to trail the currency movement automatically.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Exit Strategy</h3>
                <p>Exit your position either on the opposite signal or based on additional signals, such as Momentum crossing the 100 mark in the opposite direction.</p>
